$ Powershell: Param(Parameter(Mandatory=$true|$false))

By default, in → Windows/PowerShell, it is not required to specify a value for a → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters[parameters]
when a → Windows/PowerShell/language/function is called. With `Param([Parameter(Mandatory=$true)…])`, it is possible to make a parameter mandatory,
with `Param([Parameter(Mandatory=$false)…])`, a parameter can explicitely be marked as optional.

{ Check if parameter was passed

  The following script uses the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/psBoundParameters[automatic variable `$psBoundParameters`] to
  check if an optional parameter was specfied when script was invoked.

  gh|about-PowerShell|/language/statement/function/parameters/attributes/parameter/mandatory/psBoundParameters.ps1||

}

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters/attributes[Function and script parameter attributes]
